Mental Health - Psychosis, Schizophrenia Spectrum Disorders, and Hallucinations
The impact of sound frequencies (Hz) and amplitudes (dB) on hearing, as well as their potential role in contributing to psychosis, schizophrenia spectrum disorders, and hallucinations, is a topic that intersects with both neuroscience and psychiatry.
Abnormal sound perception or prolonged exposure to certain frequencies and loudness can influence mental health, particularly in individuals predisposed to psychosis or hallucinations. 
Hereâ€™s how different sound frequencies and amplitudes might affect these conditions:





